 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 12: THERE ARE NOT FIVE SYSTEMS. There is ONE system with five SOURCES of context blocks. The ceremony level isn't a 'decision about methodology enforcement.' It's a context block that says 'follow this process' competing for token budget against blocks that say 'do this task' or 'check this boundary.' The harvest warning isn't a 'decision about when to harvest.' It's a context block that says 'run braid harvest' competing against all other blocks. Every output of the system is a context block. Every context block has an expected_delta_fs and a cost (tokens). The acquisition function alpha = expected_delta_fs / tokens handles ALL of them. CONSEQUENCE: ceremony_level() and harvest_urgency_multi() don't need to be 'integrated' into the acquisition function. They need to be RECOGNIZED as already being context blocks that should be scored by the acquisition function. The separate functions exist because we didn't see that all system outputs are the same type. UAQ-7 and UAQ-8 become: ensure ceremony and harvest recommendation blocks are scored and ranked alongside task and coherence blocks. No new scoring logic — just ensure these blocks carry AcquisitionScore. The architecture simplifies because the insight removes a false distinction. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-025, INV-FOUNDATION-011."
